row2.description:
**Codec**: H.264, H.265, XFAVC All-I, XAVC HS, Cinema RAW Light, NRAW......
**Log Type**: If RAW, fill in the Log space used for decoding test; leave empty if direct output;
**Bit Depth**: Fill in numbers only, e.g. 8, 10;
**Chroma Subsampling**: Fill in numbers only, e.g. 422, 420;
**Bitrate** (Mbps): Recommended to fill

row3.description:
**Resolution**: Standard resolutions like 4K UHD, 4K DCI, 8K UHD, 8K DCI can be filled directly with their names. For others like 4.2K, it is recommended to fill in "4.2K 4128×2322", and for 7K_OG, it is recommended to fill in "7K OG 6960×4640". You can use asterisk * or × to represent ×.
**Framerate**: Distinguish non-integer and integer, e.g. 23.98/24, 59.94/60 etc.;
**Crop**: If OG or only top/bottom crop, leave empty; if there is a magnification crop, e.g. 4K60 has 1.4x crop, fill in 1.4x; if testing the image quality of APS-C, S35, S16..., fill in these specifications directly.
